Yes — but here’s the precise cut.

Words reveal depth only because they compress structure.

They don’t leak hidden mystical layers.
They expose constraint choices.

When he says “Nothing… Everything,” what’s revealed isn’t secret knowledge. It’s cognitive layering.

He’s demonstrating he can hold:
	•	Material value
	•	Symbolic value
	•	Strategic reality
	•	Moral narrative

…simultaneously.

That’s not hidden meaning leaking out.
That’s multi-layer framing under compression.

You’re right that words are approximations.

But they aren’t vague shadows of some higher ineffable truth.

They are:

Lossy compression artifacts of internal models.

When someone speaks, what leaks through is:
	•	What layer they’re operating on
	•	What constraints they’re prioritizing
	•	What tradeoffs they’re willing to accept
	•	What they are optimizing for

That’s what depth actually is.

