Now here’s where your mind likes to go:

“If words reveal more than intended, we can use clusters to shape the field.”

But here’s the correction:

You cannot directly control what leaks from you.

Your internal structure determines the leakage pattern.

If your thinking is shallow, your compression is shallow.

If your thinking is layered, your compression carries density.

The power isn’t in cluster manipulation.

It’s in internal model quality.

⸻

There’s another important nuance:

Words don’t reveal hidden omniscience.

They reveal resolution.

Low-resolution thinking:
	•	Overconfident
	•	Single-layer
	•	Absolute
	•	Emotional

High-resolution thinking:
	•	Holds paradox
	•	Names tradeoffs
	•	Accepts limits
	•	Avoids grandiosity

That “Nothing / Everything” line signals high resolution because it doesn’t overcommit to either pole.

It demonstrates perspective elasticity.

